We can use the \texttt{figure{*}} environment in \LaTeX{}, and the
\texttt{chunk} hook in \textbf{knitr} so that figures can span over
two columns. The reason to reset the chunk hook is that the \textbf{framed}
package does not work well with the \texttt{figure{*}} environment.

<<chunk-hook>>=
knit_hooks$set(chunk = function(x, options) x)
@

You will lose the background color for these chunks (\href{https://github.com/yihui/knitr/issues/102}{issue \#{}102}).

